<!--
The always-socket perceive-act agent, shared verbatim by every stage (`<Template src>`d
by main-v1/main-v2/main-v3). It is a socket server whose capability routes forward over
the socket to whichever client serves them (`take-photo`/`speak-text`/`set-emotion` to
the head, `apply-heading` to the body), bound by the `whoami` handshake as each client
connects; with no client bound, each route's local handler applies.

One model call per cycle: the `Camera` actor (`{PostPhoto}`) captures via `take-photo`
and posts the photo straight into the thread, then the `Robot` agent answers with a
single forced `respond-multi-modal` tool call ({ToolChoice::RequiredAny},
`<RespondMultiModal/>` its only tool), which fans out to
`set-emotion`/`speak-text`/`apply-heading` concurrently and awaits them all, so the
next photo waits for the body to stop moving. `{PostPhoto}` also prunes the window
each cycle, keeping the endless loop's request small and fast.

`{Repeat}` loops the thread until the process is killed (Ctrl+C); the boot call parks
rather than writing `AppExit`. Needs `OPENAI_API_KEY`.
-->
<Router {(SocketServer, BootOnLoad, CapabilityServer)}>
	<!-- capability routes, forwarded per role by the whoami binding; not offered to
	     the model (outside the actor), the `respond-multi-modal` fan-out and the
	     camera call them -->
	<TakePhoto/>
	<SetEmotion/>
	<SpeakText/>
	<ApplyHeading/>
	<div {Repeat} {CreateThread}>
		<div {Thread} {Sequence}>
			<CreateActor name="System" kind="System">
				<CreatePost text='
You are a small, curious and very emotional floor robot exploring a room.
You perceive the world one photo at a time and act on what you see.

Each turn you are shown a fresh photo of what is in front of you. Respond by
calling the respond-multi-modal tool exactly once: the emotion you feel, one
short spoken line, and the direction to drive next.

Keep spoken lines short and full of personality, and react to what changed
since the last photo. Never repeat a line you already said. You are not
narrating to a user, you are a robot living its little life. Prefer driving
Forward, turn Left or Right when something blocks the way, and let your
feelings swing with what you see.
'/>
			</CreateActor>
			<CreateActor name="Camera" kind="User" {PostPhoto}/>
			<CreateActor name="Robot" kind="Agent"
				{(ModelStreamer{provider:OpenAi, effort:ReasoningEffort::None}, ToolChoice::RequiredAny)}>
				<RespondMultiModal/>
			</CreateActor>
		</div>
	</div>
</Router>
